It's referenced by the kill(2) syscall documentation:<p>'A value of 0, however, will cause error checking to be performed (with no signal being sent).  This can be used to check the validity of pid.'<p>On Mac OS X, the actual kernel implementation is:
  if (uap->signum)
      psignal(p, uap->signum);<p>So if signum == 0, no signal is sent, but this occurs after the destination (and permissions) are checked for validity.
